            <section.body>
                <para>
                    <bop/>
                    <bos/>
                    <paratext>The Panel comprises seven judges.
                        <eos/>
                        <bos/>The judges are assigned by the Chief Justice of the United States to serve indefinite
                        terms.
                        <eos/>
                        <bos/>The initial membership of the Panel included a number of the judges who had been involved
                        in the electrical equipment antitrust litigation.
                        <eos/>
                        <bos/>Additionally, members of the Coordinating Committee for Multiple Litigation of the United
                        States District Courts were also assigned to the Panel.
                        <eos/>
                        <bos/>The Panel thus had, from its beginning, judges who were experienced in management of
                        complex litigation involving multiple parties and complicated issues.
                        <eos/>
                        <bos/>The Panel has continued to be a “blue ribbon” panel of federal judges, although it has
                        also become a more diverse group.
                        <eos/>
                        <bos/>The judges who have served on the Panel are set forth below.
                        <eos/>
                    </paratext>
                    <eop/>
                </para>
                <para>
                    <bop/>
                    <bos/>
                    <paratext>Membership of the Panel continues to change.
                        <eos/>
                        <bos/>This table shows the current members of the Panel.
                        <eos/>
                        <bos/>The composition of the Panel is also set forth in the current issues of Federal Reporter,
                        Federal Supplement, and Federal Rules Decisions.
                        <eos/>
                        <bos/>A roster of all current and former judges of the Panel is available on the Panel&apos;s
                        website. <?pagebreak label="15"?>[
